> Jared,
> I wanted to take a minute and provide an update relative to the progress we are making with First
> Data. As we discussed, we have asked for a change to the current agreement we have in place with
> them. We now share a "most favored nations" clause with each other and we have agreed to
> eliminate this provision from our agreement. Both teams have agreed in principal, however this will
> require an amendment. An amendment has a long pole in the tent due to the legal process, approvals,
> notifications, etc. In addition, we have a "disconnect" with their legal and business teams. The legal
> team has been instructed they cannot work on this amendment based on not having clarity relative to
> the interpretation of anti-trust issues surrounding this clause if we are to complete the transaction
> with you. Their actions are based solely on an abundance of caution. We met with the business
> team today and they are 100% behind making the change and realize the exposure created by doing
> nothing is far greater than moving forward with reasonable changes.
>

>
> 1.  We have asked our General Counsel to reach out to their General Counsel to discuss the issue.
